review_blob: Aroma is fairly mild; chocolate, cola, and a little woody. Amazingly thick and dark with a thick beige head. Taste is roasted malts, cola, coffee, and chocolate, with big bitterness to finish. Big body, smooth mouthful. Lovely.
beer_name: Mikkeller X-mas Porter 2013 Via Til Fra (Via To From)

review_blob: Nice aroma, mango, yeast and malt. Golden cloudy. Refreshing and quite bitter, subtle mango and orange complimented by the yeast. Good mouthfeel. Nice but no show stopper.

Aroma is subtle, sweet malts plus a little alcohol and fishy undertones. Head didnt last at all. Taste is a subtle mix of chocolate and coffee malts, a hint of alcohol and medium, earthy, bitterness. Great mouthfeel thanks to its big body. A nice beer.
A very good beer to begin with, add a bit of a sour twist and it just gets better. Quite bitter, but smooth, good body, and a nice kick from the wild yeast.

Everything you want, flavour-wise from a coffee stout, lots of coffee complimented by the bitterness and flavour of the hops. Mouth feel is good, lots of body and gentle carbonation. Absolutely no head after a minute and not much aroma. Damn good for the style though.
A tasty number but it underdelivers on juniper. A nice aroma, malty body and well balanced bitterness to finish.

A rather bitter wee number, plenty of alcohol in the aroma but its not so noticeable in the flavour. Lots of roasted flavours giving some dirty coffee notes. A little syrupy but relatively little body for such a strong beer. A satisfying strong, bitter stout (you will love it if you are looking for those three things).

@ZBF. Wifey says "smells like a fresh baked cake, I could smell it all day". Lots of coffee and chocolate in aroma and taste. Excellent mouth feel, nice full body. Not sweet, gentle bitterness to finish. A very satisfying stout.
Not what Im looking for in a stout. A little pale, not much roast make goodness. Quite spicy and sweet but a bitter finish. Too much alcohol too.

Tap @ZBF. Gentle aroma, sweet malts and citrus. Nice golden colour, decent head retention. Full body yeasty malts hit first followed by sour oak coconut and citrus hop flavors and big bitterness to finish (combined with lingering sourness) Great mouth feel.
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar La Renaissance Bronze (1/2 Year barrel aged)

review_blob: Tried at zythos, from the tap served too cold. Subtle nose, yeasty with a hint of lemon. Pale cloudy lemon colour with good head retention. Gentle body, easy drinking. Citrus and yeast flavours with some coconut hop notes. Not much bitterness, a little watery, easy drinking.

I?m a sucker for a dark sour, and this guy satisfies me plenty. Aroma is sour with nice roasted malt undertones. From the tap at zythos. No head, dark brown. Light carbonation and body, but the real winner is the taste, hits you with sourness first then you get some subtle roasted malts followed by gentle bitterness. You?d never guess it?s 10%. A great example of the style.

From the tap at zythos. Super refreshing, lovely hoppy nose with orange-yeast undertones. Light body with nice hop/fruit flavor. Lemon notes too, with a mid to strong bitterness to finish. Nice and cloudy in the glass. Excellent.

beer_name: Emelisse White Label Imperial Russian Stout (Ardbeg BA)
